      • PrintJobJson

        public PrintJobJson(int printerId,
            java.lang.String title,
            java.lang.String contentType,
            java.lang.String content,
            java.lang.String source)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Creates an object to be serialized into JSON. Requires a contentType - if contentType is base_64, it is encoded into base64.
        Parameters:
        printerId - id of the printer which wil run the PrintJob.
        title - title of the printjob.
        contentType - Type of content. base64, uri, etc.
        content - either a file, or a URL to a file. Depends on contentType.
        source - Would be from the PrintNode-Java client.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
